Now I understand the issue. The script `run.sh` lacks a global trap for cleanup - when interrupted, spinner processes and agent child processes become orphaned. There's already `stop_spinner()` at line 415 and `cleanup_dev_server()` at line 2626, but no global `trap cleanup EXIT INT TERM`.

